(166, 1, '2014-12-30 23:35:21', '2014-12-30 23:35:21', 'Sometimes our projects have been focused just on the frontend side of the web development. In this context, we tend to use bootstraps layouts (always responsive, of course), and lately trying another framework called Flat UI (an extension of Bootstrap). Here just some of the examples of our frontend projects.\n<h3>Integration Kendo UI and Twitter Bootstrap</h3>\nWe were entitled this task from Willis Ltd, and the main idea was to integrate the Kendo components (Kendo is a library with components like sliders, input boxes, tooltips etc) with the layout of twitter Bootstrap.\n\nA demo of this job can be found <a href="http://www.cobianzo.com/test/" target="_blank">here</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Somo Global Landing page</h3>\n<a class="pull-left" href="http://somo-holding-page.mitreum.net/products-and-platforms/"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-165" src="SITEURL/wp-content/uploads/somo-holding-portrait-311x400.gif" alt="somo-holding-portrait" width="311" height="400" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nDuring our project of Netgig for Somo global we were asked to develop in a single day the holding page for the company, following the specs of an internal graphic designer.\n\n<a href="http://somo-holding-page.mitreum.net/" target="_blank">Here the result</a>', 'Just front end jobs', 'We work also as frontend developers under demand. Here some of the examples', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '164-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-12-30 23:35:21', '2014-12-30 23:35:21', '', 164, 'SITEURL/164-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(163, 1, '2014-12-30 19:14:22', '2014-12-30 19:14:22', '', 'yco-apaisado', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'yco-apaisado', '', '', '2014-12-30 19:14:22', '2014-12-30 19:14:22', '', 162, 'SITEURL/wp-content/uploads/yco-apaisado.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(164, 1, '2010-12-30 19:57:20', '2010-12-30 19:57:20', 'Sometimes our projects have been focused just on the frontend side of the web development. In this context, we tend to use bootstraps layouts (always responsive, of course), and lately trying another framework called Flat UI (an extension of Bootstrap). Here just some of the examples of our frontend projects.\r\n<h3>Integration Kendo UI and Twitter Bootstrap</h3>\r\nWe were entitled this task from Willis Ltd, and the main idea was to integrate the Kendo components (Kendo is a library with components like sliders, input boxes, tooltips etc) with the layout of twitter Bootstrap.\r\n\r\nA demo of this job can be found <a href="http://www.cobianzo.com/test/" target="_blank">here</a>\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-172" src="SITEURL/wp-content/uploads/willis-whole-page-400x174.jpg" alt="willis-whole-page" width="400" height="174" />\r\n<h3>Somo Global Landing page</h3>\r\n<a class="pull-left" href="http://somo-holding-page.mitreum.net/products-and-platforms/"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-165" src="SITEURL/wp-content/uploads/somo-holding-portrait-311x400.gif" alt="somo-holding-portrait" width="311" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDuring our project of Netgig for Somo global we were asked to develop in a single day the holding page for the company, following the specs of an internal graphic designer.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://somo-holding-page.mitreum.net/" target="_blank">Here the result</a>', 'Just front end jobs', 'We work also as frontend developers under demand. Here some of the examples', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'just-front-end-jobs', '', '', '2014-12-30 23:35:46', '2014-12-30 23:35:46', '', 0, 'SITEURL/?post_type=work&#038;p=164', 0, 'work', '', 0),
